\vspace{0.2em}\noindent\textbf{(iv) Calibration robustness and reproducibility (R1 YciJ).}
Calibration aims to estimate stable principal directions (PCA) for later transformation, not to learn new capabilities.
Empirically, it is robust to calibration scale. Results reported in our paper can be reached using $\sim$128k \textbf{text} tokens from WikiText2 with \textbf{8000} calibration steps, freezing the vision tower.
We swept the calibration sequence length from 16k to 256k. As shown in Table~\ref{tab:calib}, PPL on WikiText2 remains highly stable (range $<0.02$), confirming that the projection matrices stabilize efficiently with minimal data.
