\vspace{0.2em}\noindent\textbf{Recovery training amount (R2 THCN).}
We study a lightweight recovery (8$\times$A100, effective batch size 16, 15k steps). Baseline on VideoMME is 63\%; after migration, 200-step alignment already reaches 57\% (90.5\% of baseline), 700 steps: 58.6\% (93\%), 3k: 60.5\% (94.1\%), and $\sim$8k reaches the reported best. This indicates recovery is not brittle and most performance is restored quickly.
